\f1\b0  HI!!! How many of you are visual designers? User experience? Developers? Project Managers? Other? I think it\'92s safe to assume we\'92re all here because we design or build digital experiences in some capacity.\
\
I want to talk about our assumptions about users. In day-to-day work as digital craftspeople, we don\'92t think beyond our own abilities. We assume people can use the mouse, appreciate subtle expressions of color and understand visual communications. I want to challenge these assumptions and open your minds to a broader definition of user experience. Reflective of more people in the world.\
\

